From 15 December 2021, many temporary visa holders, including subclass 408 visa holders(Djokovic was granted this visa in Nov 2021), can travel to Australia without needing to apply for exemption if fully vaccinated, because he is unvaccinated, and he did not apply for individual exemption before came to Australia. He had also his income declaration form he did not travel within 14 days  prior to come Australia, in fact he trained in Spain around Christmas. Yes the Tennis Australia,(or two doctors appointed by Tennis Australia) issued him an exemption letter, most likely they've  done Djokovic a favour at his request, ofcause Djokovic and Tennis Australia known the answer.  

Tennis Australia is owned by states/territories, Australian Border is Commonwealth matter. 

If he had applied for individual exemption and told the Australian authority that he had travelled to Spain around Christmas sure things would turned out differently.
